# CODEOWNERS
#
# GitHub uses this file to auto-request reviews on PRs that touch the
# listed paths. When branch protection has "Require review from Code
# Owners" enabled on `main`, a PR touching any path below CANNOT be
# merged without an approving review from the matched owner(s).
#
# Owner handle used below: @security-owners
#   Replace with the actual GitHub team slug (e.g. @your-org/security)
#   or an individual user handle (e.g. @alice). The handle MUST exist
#   in the repo's organization and have at least read access, or GitHub
#   silently ignores the rule.
#
# Last matching pattern wins (unlike .gitignore). Keep security rules
# at the bottom so they override any broader default owner added later.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# Security CI + scan logic
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------

# CI workflow — controls which jobs run on PRs (security linter,
# migrations-against-fresh-DB, RLS/tamper regression tests, types diff,
# checkout verification). Widening allowlists or removing a job here
# is a security-sensitive change.
/.github/workflows/ci.yml              @security-owners

# Any future workflow files also get security review by default.
/.github/workflows/                    @security-owners

# CODEOWNERS itself — only security can change who owns security paths.
/.github/CODEOWNERS                    @security-owners

# Supabase database-linter runner + APPROVED_ALLOWLIST rationale gate.
# Changes here can suppress security findings, so require review.
/scripts/supabase-security-lint.mjs    @security-owners

# Baseline of accepted database-linter findings — every added
# fingerprint is an accepted security finding by definition.
/security/                             @security-owners
/security/lint-baseline.json           @security-owners

# Database migrations shape RLS policies, GRANTs, SECURITY DEFINER
# functions, and field-tamper triggers. All security-relevant.
/supabase/migrations/                  @security-owners

# SQL regression tests that guard RLS + tamper triggers on rsvps etc.
/supabase/tests/                       @security-owners

# Top-level security posture doc.
/SECURITY.md                           @security-owners
